# Blog Images Folder

This folder stores uploaded blog images.

## Folder Structure


public/blog-images/
├── featured/          # Featured/hero images for blogs
│   ├── blog-1-hero.jpg
│   └── blog-2-hero.jpg
├── inline/            # Images used within blog content
│   ├── img-1704067200000-abc123.jpg
│   ├── img-1704067300000-def456.jpg
│   └── ...
└── archive/           # Archived images (for cleanup)
```

## Image Organization

- **featured/**: Large images used as blog headers (optimized for 1200x630px)
- **inline/**: Images inserted into blog content (optimized for readability)
- **archive/**: Removed/replaced images (kept for backup)

## File Naming Convention

- Auto-generated: `img-{timestamp}-{randomId}.jpg`
- Featured images: `blog-{blogId}-hero.jpg`
- Organized by type for easy management

## Image Optimization

All uploaded images are automatically:
- Compressed to reduce file size
- Resized to max 1200px width
- Converted to optimal format (JPEG for photos, PNG for graphics)
- Validated before storage

## Access

Published blog images are served at:
- `/blog-images/[folder]/[filename]`

Example: `/blog-images/inline/img-1704067200000-abc123.jpg`

## Storage Management

- Monitor localStorage usage in blog editor
- Archive old images when needed
- Use CDN for improved delivery
- Consider cloud storage (Supabase) for scale
